# Simple Text Style

Enforces a typographic grid.

The approach is based on the following influences:
Grid Systems
Tightly based headers (for h2 & h3), based on Robin Williams recommendations. (Cross referenced with well typeset magazines like the Economist, The New Yorker, and Wired.)
Creating a vertical rhythm
Hanging punctuation

Font hierarchy from XXX

Joe Clark 


I'm convinced most web typography improperly leaves to much bottom margin under subheadings (titles, typically reserved for H1, leave much more room). 



